history.content:
-- Posting on behalf of the Society of Women Engineers --

Evening with Industry is a professional networking event hosted by SWE (Society of Women Engineers) which aims to connect students with representatives from companies of various STEM-related fields. This year, the event will be taking place in a digital space, Gatherly.io, where students and representatives can move around, connect, and start video chatting! This is your chance to make an impression and get to learn about the companies you envision yourself working for. 

Mark your calendars for Wednesday, October 21st, 6-9 PM PT! Evening with Industry is open to all Berkeley students. Complete this form between September 28st - October 16th to register and purchase your tickets: https://tinyurl.com/SWE2020EWI

If financial support is needed to buy a ticket, please email ewi.berkeley@gmail.com. 

We hope to see you there!
